results.title: Adjust Your Crown
results.excerpt:
Will you be there, at the end,
where pheasants gather,
half-spun with nesting
birds of paradise

Will you offer praise
to the night birds, keeping watch
over their kingdom with sunset eyes—
dual moons rising overhead

Or are you suspended in stasis,
the plaything of scavengers
mid-game who pause their star-pulling 
to trap you instead
beware of offers half-decided
pull yourself from hibernation 
before it’s too late
to tell the difference 
between Spring and death,
sleep and forest fires

Are you proud of the thoughts
you swallowed mid-flutter
freed from gilded cages,
ellipses strewn….about

The time for teeth and claws,
flashing conflict has passed
wild eyes turned blind
in the daylight

Take cover in the shade of sunflowers
for a soft and fuzzy drink puddling
in warm colors at your feet

Cuddle in the arms that bleed flowers
and piebald warmth against your chest
